```

In this code, we create a `Row` with the `Arrangement.SpaceEvenly` parameter to evenly space all of our buttons across the row.

Inside the row, we use the `Box` composable to wrap each `Button`. We give each `Box` a `weight` of 1f to evenly distribute the horizontal space between each button. We also add a `padding` of 8.dp to add some margin between the `Button` and the `Box`.

Finally, we set the modifier of each `Button` to `Modifier.fillMaxSize()` which makes each button the same size as the containing `Box`. This ensures that all buttons have the same size and they are evenly distributed across the row.

